#: ../../../Security.rst:3
msgid "LLVM Security Response Group"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../Security.rst:5
msgid "The LLVM Security Response Group has the following goals:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../Security.rst:7
msgid ""
"Allow LLVM contributors and security researchers to disclose security-"
"related issues affecting the LLVM project to members of the LLVM community."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../Security.rst:8
msgid "Organize fixes, code reviews, and release management for said issues."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../Security.rst:9
msgid ""
"Allow distributors time to investigate and deploy fixes before wide "
"dissemination of vulnerabilities or mitigation shortcomings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../Security.rst:10
msgid ""
"Ensure timely notification and release to vendors who package and distribute "
"LLVM-based toolchains and projects."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../Security.rst:11
msgid ""
"Ensure timely notification to users of LLVM-based toolchains whose compiled "
"code is security-sensitive, through the `CVE process`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../Security.rst:13
msgid ""
"*Note*: these goals ensure timely action, provide disclosure timing when "
"issues are reported, and respect vendors' / packagers' / users' constraints."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../Security.rst:15
msgid ""
"The LLVM Security Response Group is private. It is composed of trusted LLVM "
"contributors. Its discussions remain within the LLVM Security Response Group "
"(plus issue reporter and key experts) while an issue is being investigated. "
"After an issue becomes public, the entirety of the group’s discussions "
"pertaining to that issue also become public."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../Security.rst:20
msgid "How to report a security issue?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../Security.rst:22
msgid ""
"To report a security issue in any of the LLVM projects, please use the "
"`report a vulnerability`_ feature in the `llvm/llvm-security-repo`_ "
"repository on github, under the \"Security\" tab."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../Security.rst:24
msgid ""
"We aim to acknowledge your report within two business days since you first "
"reach out. If you do not receive any response by then, you can escalate by "
"posting on the `Discourse forums`_ asking to get in touch with someone from "
"the LLVM Security Response Group. **The escalation mailing list is public**: "
"avoid discussing or mentioning the specific issue when posting on it."
msgstr ""

