#: ../../../Security.rst:64
msgid "Criteria"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../Security.rst:66
msgid ""
"Nominees for LLVM Security Response Group membership should fall in one of "
"these groups:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../Security.rst:68
msgid "Individual contributors:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../Security.rst:70
msgid ""
"Specializes in fixing compiler-based security related issues or often "
"participates in their exploration and resolution."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../Security.rst:71 ../../../Security.rst:77
msgid ""
"Has a track record of finding security vulnerabilities and responsible "
"disclosure of those vulnerabilities."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../Security.rst:72 ../../../Security.rst:78
msgid ""
"Is a compiler expert who has specific interests in knowing about, resolving, "
"and preventing future security vulnerabilities."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../Security.rst:73
msgid ""
"Has actively contributed non-trivial code to the LLVM project in the last "
"year."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../Security.rst:75
msgid "Researchers:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../Security.rst:80
msgid "Vendor contacts:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../Security.rst:82
msgid ""
"Represents an organization or company which ships products that include "
"their own copy of LLVM. Due to their position in the organization, the "
"nominee has a reasonable need to know about security issues and disclosure "
"embargoes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../Security.rst:84
msgid ""
"Additionally, the following are necessary but not sufficient criteria for "
"membership in the LLVM Security Response Group:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../Security.rst:86
msgid ""
"If already in the LLVM Security Response Group, has actively participated in "
"one (if any) security issue in the last year."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../Security.rst:87
msgid ""
"If already in the LLVM Security Response Group, has actively participated in "
"most membership discussions in the last year."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../Security.rst:88
msgid ""
"If already in the LLVM Security Response Group, has actively participated in "
"writing or reviewing a transparency report in the last year."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../Security.rst:89
msgid ""
"When employed by a company or other entity, the parent entity has no more "
"than three members already in the LLVM Security Response Group."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../Security.rst:90
msgid ""
"When nominated as a vendor contact, their position with that vendor remains "
"the same as when originally nominated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../Security.rst:91
msgid ""
"Nominees are trusted by existing LLVM Security Response Group members to "
"keep communications embargoed while still active."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../Security.rst:94
msgid "Nomination process"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../Security.rst:96
msgid ""
"Anyone who feels they meet these criteria can nominate themselves, or may be "
"nominated by a third party such as an existing LLVM Security Response Group "
"member. The nomination should state whether the nominee is nominated as an "
"individual, researcher, or as a vendor contact. It should clearly describe "
"the grounds for nomination."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../Security.rst:98
msgid ""
"For the moment, nominations are generally proposed, discussed, and voted on "
"using a github pull request. An `example nomination is available here`_. The "
"use of pull requests helps keep membership discussions open, transparent, "
"and easily accessible to LLVM developers in many ways. If, for any reason, a "
"fully-world-readable nomination seems inappropriate, you may reach out to "
"the LLVM Security Response Group via the `report a vulnerability`_ route, "
"and a discussion can be had about the best way to approach nomination, given "
"the constraints that individuals are under."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../Security.rst:101
msgid "Choosing new members"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../Security.rst:103
msgid ""
"If a nomination for LLVM Security Response Group membership is supported by "
"a majority of existing LLVM Security Response Group members, then it carries "
"within five business days unless an existing member of the Security Response "
"Group objects. If an objection is raised, the LLVM Security Response Group "
"members should discuss the matter and try to come to consensus; failing "
"this, the nomination will succeed only by a two-thirds supermajority vote of "
"the LLVM Security Response Group."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../Security.rst:106
msgid "Accepting membership"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../Security.rst:108
msgid ""
"Before new LLVM Security Response Group membership is finalized, the "
"successful nominee should accept membership and agree to abide by this "
"security policy, particularly `Privileges and Responsibilities of LLVM "
"Security Response Group Members`_ below."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../Security.rst:111
msgid "Keeping Membership Current"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../Security.rst:113
msgid ""
"At least every six months, the LLVM Security Response Group applies the "
"above criteria. The membership list is pruned accordingly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../Security.rst:114
msgid ""
"Any LLVM Security Response Group member can ask that the criteria be applied "
"within the next five business days."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../Security.rst:115
msgid ""
"If a member of the LLVM Security Response Group does not act in accordance "
"with the letter and spirit of this policy, then their LLVM Security Response "
"Group membership can be revoked by a majority vote of the members, not "
"including the person under consideration for revocation. After a member "
"calls for a revocation vote, voting will be open for five business days."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../Security.rst:116
msgid ""
"Emergency suspension: an LLVM Security Response Group member who blatantly "
"disregards the LLVM Security Policy may have their membership temporarily "
"suspended on the request of any two members. In such a case, the requesting "
"members should notify the LLVM Security Response Group with a description of "
"the offense. At this point, membership will be temporarily suspended for "
"five business days, pending outcome of the vote for permanent revocation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../Security.rst:117
msgid ""
"The LLVM Board may remove any member from the LLVM Security Response Group."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../Security.rst:120
msgid "Transparency Report"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../Security.rst:122
msgid ""
"Every year, the LLVM Security Response Group must publish a transparency "
"report. The intent of this report is to keep the community informed by "
"summarizing the disclosures that have been made public in the last year. It "
"shall contain a list of all public disclosures, as well as statistics on "
"time to fix issues, length of embargo periods, and so on."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../Security.rst:124
msgid ""
"The transparency reports are published at :doc:`SecurityTransparencyReports`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../Security.rst:128
msgid "Privileges and Responsibilities of LLVM Security Response Group Members"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../Security.rst:131
msgid "Access"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../Security.rst:133
msgid ""
"LLVM Security Response Group members will be subscribed to a private "
"`Discussion Medium`_. It will be used for technical discussions of security "
"issues, as well as process discussions about matters such as disclosure "
"timelines and group membership. Members have access to all security issues."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../Security.rst:136
msgid "Confidentiality"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../Security.rst:138
msgid ""
"Members of the LLVM Security Response Group will be expected to treat LLVM "
"security issue information shared with the group as confidential until "
"publicly disclosed:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../Security.rst:140
msgid ""
"Members should not disclose security issue information to non-members unless "
"both members are employed by the same vendor of a LLVM based product, in "
"which case information can be shared within that organization on a need-to-"
"know basis and handled as confidential information normally is within that "
"organization."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../Security.rst:141
msgid ""
"If the LLVM Security Response Group agrees, designated members may share "
"issues with vendors of non-LLVM based products if their product suffers from "
"the same issue. The non-LLVM vendor should be asked to respect the issue’s "
"embargo date, and to not share the information beyond the need-to-know "
"people within their organization."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../Security.rst:142
msgid ""
"If the LLVM Security Response Group agrees, key experts can be brought in to "
"help address particular issues. The key expert should be asked to respect "
"the issue’s embargo date, and to not share the information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../Security.rst:145
msgid "Disclosure"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../Security.rst:147
msgid ""
"Following the process below, the LLVM Security Response Group decides on "
"embargo date for public disclosure for each Security issue. An embargo may "
"be lifted before the agreed-upon date if all vendors planning to ship a fix "
"have already done so, and if the reporter does not object."
msgstr ""

